items.description:
Preferred host for the AI model.
 'GitHub' means user explicitly asks for GitHub hosted models, or calls 'models.inference.ai.azure.com', or 'models.github.ai', or uses GitHub token to access model;
 'AzureAIFoundry' means user explicitly asks for Azure AI Foundry hosted models, or calls '*.ai.azure.com', or '*.openai.azure.com';
 'OpenAI' means user explicitly asks for OpenAI hosted models, or calls 'api.openai.com', or uses openai SDK with default endpoint;
 'Anthropic' means user explicitly asks for Anthropic hosted models, or calls 'api.anthropic.com', or uses anthropic SDK;
 'Google' means user explicitly asks for Google hosted models, or calls '*.googleapis.com', or uses google generativeai SDK;
 'other' means none of above.
